# outline-64 — Spindle load script
#
# First paragraph: auto-loaded by Spindle's boot loader, jumped to.
# Subsequent paragraphs: loaded on each jsr $c90 from running code.

# Part 1: loading screen at $c000 — auto-loaded by Spindle's boot
# loader. Hand-off to main: jsr $c90 + jmp $0810.
parts/screenfill/screenfill.prg

# Part 2: main demo, extracted as chunks from a single PRG so we don't
# write through Spindle's resident loader at $0c00..$0dff. Byte counts
# MUST match KickAssembler's emitted segment sizes (see ./build.sh
# output); if a segment grows past its count here the trailing bytes
# are silently truncated and the demo crashes to BASIC READY at boot.
# Format: <file>  <load_addr>  <file_offset>  <byte_count>
# main.prg's PRG load address is $0400, data starts at offset $02.
# BitmapScreenRAM (1000 bytes)
parts/main/main.prg   400   2      3e8
# Main code + IRQs                  ($0810..$0a46 = $237 bytes)
parts/main/main.prg   810   412    237
# Music (SID player + patterns)     ($1000..$1275 = $276 bytes)
parts/main/main.prg   1000  c02    276
# Bitmap (logo data, 8000 bytes)
parts/main/main.prg   2000  1c02   1f40
# Tables (palette, sines, bounce, rainbow_pal)
parts/main/main.prg   4000  3c02   800
# BmpScroll renderer + scroll text  ($5400..$5bbc = $7bd bytes)
parts/main/main.prg   5400  5002   7bd

# Part 3: end ("to be continued..." placeholder). Loads at $c000,
# overwriting the dead screenfill region. Main's outro hand-off
# (`jsr $c90 / jmp $c000`) lands here.
parts/end/end.prg     c000   2     6d
